+5 outstanding fixes from the Credora Website Content Changes PDF:
+
+1. HOME — FluidTimeline Step 02 body
+   'Deep-Dive into Financials' -> 'Deep-Dive into Your Financials and Credit Profile'
+
+2. HOME — FluidTimeline Step 03 body
+   'Strengthen application.' -> 'We analyse and strengthen your application.'
+
+3. FUND RAISING — Avg TAT stat was rendering as '314 days' because the
+   CountUp renderer stripped the en-dash via parseInt(value.replace(/[^0-9]/g,'')).
+   Fix: update data to use en-dash '3-14' -> '3–14', and update the
+   stat renderer on the fund-raising page to detect non-numeric stat values
+   and render them verbatim (no animation) instead of forcing parseInt.
+
+4. PRE-UNDERWRITING — FAQ answer for 'Do you guarantee loan approval?'
+   was missing its opening context sentence. Restored full sentence:
+   'While we significantly improve approval chances, no one can guarantee
+   approval as the final decision rests with the lender. However, our
+   pre-underwritten applications have an 95% approval rate and some other
+   application factor may get delayed loan approvals.'
+
+5. CONTACT — Removed the office-building hero image entirely (per spec)
+   along with its now-unused next/image import.
+
+Also fixed the same Step 02 / Step 03 strings in two parallel but unused
+data sources (HomeProcessTimeline.tsx, page.tsx processSteps) for
+consistency, including removing an extraneous 'Capitalisation' word that
+had slipped into the Step 02 description.
+
+TypeScript type check passes for all modified files.
